  <Metadata>
    <Title>SQLiRLLM: A Multi-Tier AI Framework for Adaptive SQL Injection Testing with Ethical Constraints</Title>
    <DocumentType>Design / Proposal Paper</DocumentType>
    <PageCount>4</PageCount>
    <SourceFile>-6947347350199591168_693147796446359.pdf</SourceFile>
    <Domain>Cybersecurity / Web Application Security / Machine Learning</Domain>
    <Note>Document contains architecture, methodology, dataset size, model choices, reward equation, and a qualitative comparison table. It does NOT contain detailed experiments, numeric evaluation results, or a separate results section.</Note>
  </Metadata>

  <Abstract sourcePage="1">
    <Summary>Proposes a three-tier AI-assisted SQL injection testing framework combining reinforcement learning and large language models, with embedded ethical constraints.</Summary>
    <CoreComponents>
      <Component tier="1" role="Strategy Selection" model="Q-Learning"/>
      <Component tier="2" role="Payload Generation" model="Phi-3 Mini"/>
      <Component tier="3" role="Post-Execution Analysis" model="Qwen2.5-Coder-14B"/>
    </CoreComponents>
    <Objective>Improve adaptability over static tools while keeping resource use practical and adding ethical constraints.</Objective>
  </Abstract>

  <Introduction sourcePage="1">
    <Statement>SQL injection remains a major vulnerability in modern web applications.</Statement>
    <ExistingTools>
      <Tool name="SQLMap" type="static, signature-based heuristics"/>
      <Tool name="Commercial scanners" type="static, signature-based heuristics"/>
    </ExistingTools>
    <ClaimedLimitations>
      <Limitation>Poor adaptation to application-specific logic</Limitation>
      <Limitation>Weak semantic awareness</Limitation>
      <Limitation>Susceptibility to Web Application Firewalls (WAFs)</Limitation>
    </ClaimedLimitations>
    <Motivation>Motivates learning-based approaches such as SSQLi, XPLOITSQL, and EPPTA.</Motivation>
  </Introduction>

  <ProblemStatement sourcePage="1">
    <Challenge id="efficiency-dilemma">Large models are computationally expensive; lighter RL approaches lack semantic depth.</Challenge>
    <Challenge id="missing-ethics">Ethical guardrails are missing in many prior RL systems.</Challenge>
    <Challenge id="single-tier">Single-tier designs do not combine complementary AI paradigms well.</Challenge>
  </ProblemStatement>

  <Contributions sourcePage="2">
    <Contribution>Multi-tier architecture dedicating specialized AI paradigms to distinct subtasks.</Contribution>
    <Contribution>Scalable computational efficiency by using models of different sizes per tier.</Contribution>
    <Contribution>Semantic depth achieved via PEFT/LoRA fine-tuning.</Contribution>
    <Contribution>Ethical constraints embedded directly in the RL reward structure.</Contribution>
  </Contributions>

